      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional tool that protects fundamental liberties against government overreach, ensuring the government can't infringe on core rights without a compelling reason. It has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and bodily integrity. This doctrine affirms that certain rights are so fundamental they are inherent to liberty and cannot be taken away by legislative fiat. It is the bedrock upon which modern personal freedoms are secured.",
      "source": "target",
